Right. Let's talk about buildings. Because nothing says "dynamic political union" quite like a sprawling, legally-mandated real estate portfolio. If you were looking for the legislative body of the [European Union](/European_Union), you might think there's a simple answer. You'd be wrong.

"Buildings of the European Parliament" might lead you here, but if you're looking for the ones in Brussels, the ones where most of the work actually gets done, you need to look at [Espace Léopold](/Espace_L%C3%A9opold). Don't get confused. Or do. It seems to be part of the system.

